{"word":"θανατόω","slug":"θανατόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θανατόω</b></el> <el>(θᾰνᾰτόω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ώσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> sense <el>θανατώσοιτο</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to put to death</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to mortify</i> the flesh, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to put to death by sentence</i> of law, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}